fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
A sheaf F on an r-simplicial topological space X_\bullet  induces a sheaf \delta  F on the diagonal simplicial space \delta  X_\bullet .
    It follows from the Cartier–Eilenberg–Zilber theorem that

    2170hodge-theory-iii-6.4.2.2hodge-theory-iii-6.4.2.2.xmlEquation6.4.2.2hodge-theory-iii-6.4.2         \mathrm {R}\Gamma (X_\bullet ,K)         \xrightarrow {\sim } \mathrm {R}\Gamma (\delta  X_\bullet ,\delta  K).       \tag{6.4.2.2}
